{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"[G3 child-coverage — container review of parent 1f19-adf2-ffb2-4b09 paired with THIS child (S6 1ba5: Docs — private-repo credentials, descriptive errors, ref/source semantics, HMAC trust model)]\n\nVERDICT: EMPTY G3 findings list. 4-bucket audit of this Docs child's contribution to the parent's acceptance/success criteria; every absence cross-checked against the WHOLE EIGHT-child roster (S1 6d56 materialize core, S2 70c7 cache, S2b b73c janitor, S3 fa49 gate threading, S4 30b3 attested signing, S4b e308 claim-gate ref-coherence/ADR 0002, S5 b7fa CLI/MCP surfacing). The union of children covers every parent criterion; no uncovered parent criterion is attributable to this pairing.\n\n4-bucket coverage map (parent AC -> covering child/children; THIS docs child's role + bucket):\n- AC1 (no attested gate reads working tree; all read faithful snapshot at pinned SHA) — FULLY by S1+S3. This child documents the attested/ref semantics (its AC3). Bucket: STRUCTURAL w.r.t. this docs child (Scope: \"Out: code (S1-S5)\"). Not an absence.\n- AC2 (signed verdict binds verified_at_sha via signed MANIFEST CHANNEL; no payload-schema/version change, prior sigs verify; reproducible) — FULLY by S4 (30b3 AC1/AC2). This child owns the docs half: AC3 (signs-vs-never-signs + verified_at_sha recorded for CLI+MCP) + AC4 (HMAC trust model + in-toto Statement shape), explicitly delegated by S4 (\"limits documented in S6\"). Bucket: PARTIALLY (docs half; binding behavior = S4). Not an absence.\n- AC3 (local mode reads in-place checkout AND cannot sign; source=local documented back-out) — by S3 (in-place read + back-out doc clause) + S4 (signing bar). This child documents attested-signs/local-never-signs + fail-closed-attested/local-still-runs (its AC2/AC3). Bucket: PARTIALLY (docs half). Not an absence.\n- AC4 (concurrent gates, no lock contention/corruption; cache+janitor reclaim under watermark without disrupting in-flight reads) — FULLY by S1+S2+S2b. This child documents the disk-cap behavior (its AC5). Bucket: STRUCTURAL w.r.t. mechanism. Not an absence.\n- AC5 (private-repo fetch failure surfaces descriptive actionable credential error) — SPLIT with THIS child as DOCS PRIMARY OWNER: S1 (6d56 AC5) RAISES the actionable error; this child's AC1 (README MCP-setup + docs/jira-sync-setup.md state the fetch-credential requirement + how to supply it, grep-able) + AC2 (message+remedy + fail-closed-attested/local-still-runs in a named file) own the documentation; the \"actionable\"/how-to-supply facet is precisely this child's contribution. Bucket: FULLY (raise S1 + docs here). Clean split.\n- AC6 (portable macOS+Linux: no external tar; no hardcoded /tmp; flock+mkdir fallback) — implementation FULLY by S1; this child documents REBAR_GATE_TMPDIR + the EFS/NFS flock caveat (its AC5, xref alto-fruit-punch). Bucket: FULLY (impl S1 + docs here). Clean split.\n- AC7 (operational tunables — watermark, default ref, grace/age windows — configurable with documented defaults, S2/S3) — implementation by S2b (watermark/grace/max-age/reverify) + S3 (ref/source defaults via standard rebar config + REBAR_* precedence). This child documents disk-cap/knobs (its AC5) + origin/main default + ref/source (its AC3). Bucket: PARTIALLY (documented-defaults prose facet co-owned). Not an absence.\n- AC8 (ADR captures architecture + rejected alternatives — PID-lease, payload-schema SHA binding) — authored by S2/S2b (rejected PID+heartbeat lease) + S4 (manifest-vs-payload SHA-binding decision) + S4b (ADR 0002). Bucket: STRUCTURAL w.r.t. this PROSE-docs child (ADR authored in S2/S4 per the parent note; Scope: \"Out: code (S1-S5)\"). Both named rejected alternatives have an authoring home. Not an absence.\n- AC9 (all EIGHT child stories closed; make lint + full suite green) — STRUCTURAL/meta epic-completion; covered by existence of all eight children (this is the docs story, 1 of 8) + each child's own green-bar obligation. Not an absence at this child.\n\nSuccess-criteria narrative (\"Every code-reading gate verifies a client-specified, immutable, reproducible snapshot at a pinned SHA — never the server's mutable checkout — safely under concurrent distributed use; signed verdicts bind verified_at_sha via the manifest channel (reproducible, no prior-signature breakage); local mode preserves the single-developer verify-before-push workflow\") decomposes onto AC1-AC6. This child carries the operator/agent-facing DOCUMENTATION surface the snapshot model newly requires — the new fetch-credential prerequisite, the descriptive failure behavior, the attested-signs/local-never-signs + origin/main + verified_at_sha semantics, the HMAC trust model + limits + in-toto Statement shape, and the REBAR_GATE_TMPDIR/disk-cap/EFS-NFS-flock knobs. It introduces NO behavioral obligation of its own and leaves no clause uncovered.\n\nNamed-consumer / delegation cross-checks (covered-by-named-consumer, not absences):\n- S4 (30b3) \"What\" explicitly delegates the HMAC-trust-model + in-toto Statement-shape docs to S6 (\"limits documented in S6\") — claimed here by this child's AC4.\n- S1 (6d56 AC5) defers the descriptive credential MESSAGE detail to S6 — claimed here by this child's AC1/AC2.\n- S5 (b7fa) scopes prose docs out (\"Out: prose docs (S6)\"); the ref/source PROSE semantics are claimed here by AC3 — a clean schema-text-vs-prose split (S5 owns inline outputSchema/text + documented defaults; this child owns the human prose in named, grep-able files).\nEach cross-ref resolves to a concrete AC on this child; no docs obligation named by a sibling is left unclaimed.\n\nNote (scope, NOT a G3 finding): the standing G4 dependency-gap on sibling S4 (30b3)/S4b (e308) about routing the pinned-SHA snapshot handle into plan_review/attest.py's dependency_hashes()/_rehash()/claim-gate freshness re-check is a CONSISTENCY (G4) code seam between S3/S4/S4b; it does not touch this docs child and leaves no parent criterion unclaimed.\n\nConclusion: this child cleanly covers the documentation slice of the parent criteria — it is the docs PRIMARY OWNER of parent AC5 (credential requirement + actionable remedy, grep-able) and the docs half of AC2/AC3/AC4/AC6/AC7. No parent acceptance/success criterion is left uncovered by the roster. No G3 finding for this pairing."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782532537559538001,"uuid":"4fe47085-acf8-4149-8248-92432f28fbbe"}